section.section:
"Growth-related project" means only the items set forth below:
any major capital project as defined in § 2-103.1(a)(4) of the Transportation Article, except existing transportation facilities projects as defined in § 4-101(h) of the Transportation Article, project planning as defined in § 8-610(i) of the Transportation Article, or initial project planning as defined in § 8-610(e) of the Transportation Article;
funding by the Department of Housing and Community Development for:
construction or purchase of newly constructed single family homes or purchase of loans for newly constructed single family homes under Title 4, Subtitle 2, Subtitle 3, or Subtitle 8 of the Housing and Community Development Article;
acquisition or construction of newly constructed multifamily rental housing under Title 4, Subtitle 2, Subtitle 4, or Subtitle 15 of the Housing and Community Development Article; or
State-funded neighborhood revitalization projects under Title 6 of the Housing and Community Development Article;
funding by the Department of Business and Economic Development under any of the following:
the Maryland Industrial Development Financing Authority, authorized under Title 5, Subtitle 4 of the Economic Development Article;
the Maryland Small Business Development Financing Authority, authorized under Title 5, Subtitle 5 of the Economic Development Article;
the former Maryland Energy Financing Act, authorized under former Article 83A, Title 6, Subtitle 4 of the Code, succeeded by the Maryland Industrial Development Financing Authority;
the Economic Development Opportunities Program Fund, authorized under § 7-314 of this article;
the former Maryland Competitive Advantage Financing Fund, authorized under former Article 83A, Title 5, Subtitle 13 of the Code; and
the Maryland Economic Development Assistance Authority and Fund, authorized under Title 5, Subtitle 3 of the Economic Development Article;
funding by the Department of the Environment, for any project under:
§§ 9-1601 through 9-1605 (Water Quality Revolving Loan Fund) of the Environment Article except for funding nonpoint source pollution projects;
§§ 9-420 through 9-426 (Water Supply Financial Assistance Program) of the Environment Article; and
the supplemental assistance program authorized under Title 9, Subtitle 3, Part VI of the Environment Article; and
except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, procurement or funding of projects by the Department of General Services for:
leases of property by the State governed by §§ 4-318 through 4-321 of this article; and
land acquisition governed by §§ 4-411 through 4-416 of this article.
